+--------------------------------------------------------------------+
| Six-Dimensional Space-Time Theory                                  |
|   from the let's-do-the-twistor dept.                              |
|   posted by kdawson on Wednesday April 18, @00:15 (Math)           |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/17/2223222      |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]eldavojohn writes "PhysOrg is covering an interesting year-old paper
that proposes an [1]alternative six-dimensional theory of space and time.
[2]George Sparling's proposition, based on Einstein's general relativity
and Elie Cartan's triality, is a twistor space (which I've only read of
in [3]Roger Penrose's latest work). The gist is that space-time is
modeled not by four dimensions but by six, and that the extra two
dimensions are time-like. Sparling is hoping that tests from the Large
Hadron Collider will help prove his theory. [4]The paper is heavy but the
PhysOrg article summarizes it nicely."

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/04/17/2223222

Links:
    0. mailto:djohnsop@gmu.edu
    1. http://www.physorg.com/news96027669.html
    2. http://www.math.pitt.edu/~sparling/
    3. http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4513655
    4. http://arxiv.org/abs/gr-qc/0610068


