| Ontario Proposes School Cyber-Bullying Law                         |
|   from the first-in-a-trend dept.                                  |
|   posted by kdawson on Wednesday April 18, @01:38 (Education)      |
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/17/2255245          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

nursegirl writes "Ontario announced today a proposal to change their
education act to add both [0]physical bullying and cyber-bullying to the
list of behaviors that can get a student suspended or expelled. Posting
comments, pictures, or videos attacking other students or teachers
outside of school hours will carry the risk of school punishment, if the
incident is believed to have an '[1]impact on school climate.'"

