[0]target violent movies and video games in a new bill. "Spitzer said he
wants to restrict access to these videos and games by children, similar
to motion picture regulations which prohibit youths under 17 from being
admitted to R-rated movies without a parent or adult guardian. Under
Spitzer's proposal, retailers who sell violent or degrading videos or
video games to children contrary to the rating would be sanctioned."

