| Montana Says No to Real ID, Passes Law to Deny It                  |
|   from the good-lines-in-the-sand dept.                            |
|   posted by ScuttleMonkey on Wednesday April 18, @18:17 (United Sta|
|   http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/04/18/1942200          |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

SoCalChris writes "Montana's governor signed a bill yesterday in
[0]defiance of the Real ID Act. [1]House Bill 287 [PDF] requires the
Montana Motor Vehicle Division to not implement the provisions of the
Real ID Act, and to report to the governor any attempts by any agent or
agency of the Department of Homeland Security to attempt to implement the
bill. Montana is the first state to implement such a law."

